I had to sneak this photo of Puck lounging in the hallway;  we are not allowed to photograph the belly.
After the mother moved her kittens out of my brother's truck we found one of them crying by our back steps. Mom never came back so she's ours now.

He was only 9... too young... we tried surgery’s and medication... in the end his kidneys failed.  We lit a fire... snuggled what weak purrs we could and the vet came to the house that was his home.  Pats continued through the injections and we stayed in his line of sight the whole time.  He was our warrior.  Picking up the pieces is hard now, but he’s at rest.
